Node.Notes: Judge/give a just decision/plead one's cause. Many see an implied trial where the accused asks the judge to defend him from his accusers, hence vindicate.
Many follow a number of Hebrew manuscripts, which read "arrogant men." Masoretic text and LXX has "strangers," which may refer to fellow Israelites who rebel against the God of Israel or non-Jews.
Qere is hiphil (causative stem) and Ketiv is qal (default stem). Both can be read as wish or statement. Tree assumes wish and Qere: "May he cause evil to turn on my enemies!"
Uncertain. Probably enemies better than slanderers.
